---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import DocsSubnav from '../../../../components/DocsSubnav.astro';
import MythicDivider from '../../../../components/MythicDivider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Recipe · Ticket-driven worker"
  description="Create → claim → spawn worker → complete. Every transition is auditable on the ticket record."
>
  <DocsSubnav />

  <section class="container-zana py-16">
    <p class="text-sm text-moss">
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}docs/recipes/`} class="hover:text-forest">← All recipes</a>
    </p>
    <p class="ornament mt-4 text-xs text-gold">— ticket-driven worker —</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-5xl text-forest md:text-6xl">Ticket → worker → done.</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-moss leading-relaxed">
      The <strong>ticket</strong> is Zana's unit of dispatch. Create one with
      a sized scope, spawn a worker against it, complete it when finished.
      Every transition is auditable on the ticket record. Initial status is
      always <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">backlog</code>;
      priority is <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">critical|high|medium|low</code>
      (not P0/P1).
    </p>

    <article class="prose-zana mt-12 max-w-prose space-y-10">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Native — one slash command</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">In Claude Code, the simplest path is a team. The plugin maps slots to background <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">Agent()</code> calls and wires SendMessage handoffs for you.</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code" lang="text">{`/zana:team backend-squad "Reply with PONG"
# → spawns architect + backend-dev(s) + test-writer in this session,
#   each named, each running in background, no daemon required.`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-moss">For one-off solo work without a template, spawn a single named background <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">Agent</code> directly and SendMessage from your conversation.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Daemon — full ticket lifecycle</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">When work needs to outlive the chat (CI, cron, autopilot), drive the same primitives through MCP:</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code · MCP (daemon path)" lang="text">{`zana_ticket_create({
  title: "QA-live: confirm PONG",
  description: "Reply with PONG to confirm.",
  priority: "low"
})
// → { id: "tkt_abc", status: "backlog", … }

zana_ticket_claim({
  ticketId: "tkt_abc"
})
// → { ok: true, status: "in-progress" }

zana_spawn_agent({
  profileId: "researcher",
  prompt: "Reply with the single word: PONG"
})
// → { agentId: "ag_42" }

// poll agent until state==="terminated", then:
zana_ticket_complete({
  ticketId: "tkt_abc",
  resultSummary: "Worker confirmed: PONG"
})
// → { ok: true, status: "done" }`}</CodeBlock>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Why a ticket?</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss leading-relaxed">
          The ticket is the unit of dispatch on either path — native team
          members can also claim tickets, and CI/cron jobs run against the
          same store.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss leading-relaxed">
          A ticket is a <em>contract</em>: a sized scope, a status the daemon
          can reason about, and an audit trail every step of the way. Zana
          will refuse to spawn a worker against a ticket that's already
          <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">done</code>, and
          listing tickets gives you a kanban-shaped view of what every agent
          in the workspace is currently doing.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Live test</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">
          Every line above is asserted end-to-end against real Claude in
          <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">scripts/qa/run-ticket-live.sh</code>
          — currently 7/7 passing.
        </p>
      </section>

      <MythicDivider />

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest">Next</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-moss">
          <li>· <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}docs/recipes/scheduled-agent/`} class="text-forest hover:text-berry">Scheduled agent</a> — run a worker on a cron/interval.</li>
          <li>· <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}docs/recipes/autopilot/`} class="text-forest hover:text-berry">Goal-driven autopilot</a> — chain workers behind a success criterion.</li>
          <li>· <a href="https://github.com/grebmann1/zana/blob/main/docs/RECIPES.md#tickets" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">Full ticket recipe in RECIPES.md</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
